http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/10-kg-ganja-seized-2-held/article14015843.ece

The police have seized 10 kg of ganja worth around Rs.20 lakh near Madhur here and arrested two persons in connection with the illicit trade.On a tip-off, a special squad led by Kasaragod circle inspector P.K. Sudhakaran intercepted a motorbike and seized narcotic substances kept in a plastic bag. They arrested the motorbike riders, identified as Muhammed Badshah, 19, and Muhammed Rafeeq, 20 at Shiribagilu, on Thursday evening.“Thadiyan” Azeez, the suspected mastermind involved in the smuggling, managed to evade the police by fleeing from the spot.